Reference: Bray et al. (2006)

Schemas
The following Schemas can be used to validate PICA XML. Not all aspects of PICA are covered.
The XML Schema (XSD) is also available at https://www.loc.gov/standards/sru/recordSchemas/pica-xml-v1-0.xsd.
The Document Type Definition (DTD) defines a superset of PICA XML without restriction on attribute values and without namespace requirement.



Listing 5.2: PICA XML XSD



&lt;?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8"?&gt;
&lt;!-- 
  PICA XML 1.0 - XML Schema for XML representation of PICA data
  Author: Jakob Voss &lt;jakob.voss@gbv.de&gt;
  Date: 2009-07-06
--&gt;
&lt;xs:schema xmlns:xs="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema" 
  targetNamespace="info:srw/schema/5/picaXML-v1.0" 
  xmlns="info:srw/schema/5/picaXML-v1.0"&gt;

  &lt;xs:element name="collection"&gt;
    &lt;xs:complexType&gt;
      &lt;xs:sequence&gt;
        &lt;xs:element minOccurs="1" maxOccurs="unbounded" ref="record"/&gt;
      &lt;/xs:sequence&gt;
    &lt;/xs:complexType&gt;
  &lt;/xs:element&gt;

  &lt;xs:element name="record" &gt;
    &lt;xs:complexType&gt;
      &lt;xs:sequence&gt;
        &lt;xs:element minOccurs="1" maxOccurs="unbounded" ref="datafield"/&gt;
      &lt;/xs:sequence&gt;
    &lt;/xs:complexType&gt;
  &lt;/xs:element&gt;

  &lt;xs:element name="datafield"&gt;
    &lt;xs:complexType&gt;
      &lt;xs:sequence&gt;
        &lt;xs:element minOccurs="1" maxOccurs="unbounded" ref="subfield"/&gt;
      &lt;/xs:sequence&gt;
      &lt;xs:attribute name="tag" use="required"&gt;
        &lt;xs:simpleType&gt;
          &lt;xs:restriction base="xs:string"&gt;
            &lt;xs:pattern value="[0-9][0-9][0-9][A-Z@]"/&gt;
          &lt;/xs:restriction&gt;
        &lt;/xs:simpleType&gt;    
      &lt;/xs:attribute&gt;
      &lt;xs:attribute name="occurrence" use="optional"&gt;
        &lt;xs:simpleType&gt;
          &lt;xs:restriction base="xs:string"&gt;
            &lt;xs:pattern value="[0-9][0-9]"/&gt;
          &lt;/xs:restriction&gt;
        &lt;/xs:simpleType&gt;    
      &lt;/xs:attribute&gt;      
    &lt;/xs:complexType&gt;
  &lt;/xs:element&gt;

  &lt;xs:element name="subfield"&gt;
    &lt;xs:complexType mixed="true"&gt;
      &lt;xs:attribute name="code" use="required"&gt;
        &lt;xs:simpleType&gt;
          &lt;xs:restriction base="xs:string"&gt;
            &lt;xs:pattern value="[0-9A-Za-z]"/&gt;
          &lt;/xs:restriction&gt;
        &lt;/xs:simpleType&gt;    
      &lt;/xs:attribute&gt;      
    &lt;/xs:complexType&gt;
  &lt;/xs:element&gt;

&lt;/xs:schema&gt;







Listing 5.3: PICA XML DTD


&lt;!ELEMENT collection (record+)&gt;
&lt;!ELEMENT record (datafield+)&gt;
&lt;!ELEMENT datafield (subfield+)&gt;
&lt;!ATTLIST datafield 
  tag CDATA #REQUIRED
  occurrence CDATA #IMPLIED&gt;
&lt;!ELEMENT subfield (#PCDATA)*&gt;
&lt;!ATTLIST subfield code CDATA #IMPLIED&gt;
